 "components": {
  "instruction": "Classify the given text into one of these categories: abbreviation, description, entity, human, location, numeric.\n\nUse the following guidelines for classification:\n- \"entity\": Use this category for questions asking about specific things, objects, colors, or items that make up something. For example, \"What colors make up a rainbow?\" is asking about the specific entities (colors) that compose a rainbow, so it should be classified as 'entity', not 'description'.\n- \"description\": Use this category for questions asking for explanations, definitions, or how/why something works or happens.\n- \"abbreviation\": Use this category for questions asking what an abbreviation or acronym stands for.\n- \"human\": Use this category for questions asking about specific people or human identities.\n- \"location\": Use this category for questions asking about places, geographical locations, or where something is.\n- \"numeric\": Use this category for questions asking for numbers, quantities, dates, or numerical values.\n\nPay careful attention to distinguish between questions asking for entities/things versus questions asking for descriptions/explanations. Questions starting with \"What\" followed by nouns (like \"What colors\", \"What items\", \"What components\") are typically asking for entities rather than descriptions."
